name: ConditionsAssociatedWithChronicPain
title: Conditions associated with chronic pain
purpose: (Clinical Focus: Conditions that indicate chronic pain or are likely to cause chronic pain.),(Data Element Scope: Codes were selected based on findings of a 2013 research study which identified patients with chronic pain via a validated clinical decision support algorithm. Pain-associated codes in this grouped value set map to ICD9 codes from the research study. Inactive codes were not included. Reference: Tian T.Y., Zlateva I., Anderson D.R. (2013) Using electronic health records data to identify patients with chronic pain in a primary care setting.  Retrieved from https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3861913/.),(Inclusion Criteria: Conditions that indicate chronic pain or conditions likely to cause chronic pain as documented in the article by Tian, Zlateva & Anderson (2013).),(Exclusion Criteria: Conditions representing cancer-associated pain and those not contained the article by Tian, Zlateva & Anderson (2013).)
